article.headline: Longwood 82, Florida Gulf Coast 75
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Antwan Carter scored a season-high 20 points to lead Longwood to an 82-75 victory over Florida Gulf Coast on Saturday in a matchup of winless teams. Dana Smith added 17 points and a game-high 12 rebounds -- his second double-double of the season -- for the Lancers (1-8), who also got a season-high 17 points from Kevin Swecker. Smith's layup with 3:14 remaining put Longwood ahead to stay, 75-73, after the Eagles (0-6) had rallied from a 12-point deficit to tie it on two free throws by Reed Baker. After Florida Gulf Coast led most of the first half, Longwood tied it, 22-22, on E.J. Dawson's 3-pointer 6:18 before halftime and took the lead on a 3-pointer by Swecker with 5:44 left. Anthony Banks, who led Florida Gulf Coast with 19 points, gave the Eagles their last lead of the half, 32-30, but Longwood's Aaron Mitchell answered with a 3-pointer 33 seconds before intermission.
